{"name": "hmd-cli-configure", "metadata": {"name": "hmd-cli-configure", "version": "1.0.39", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "", "license": "Apache 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aws-secretsmanager-caching", "boto3", "botocore", "cachetools", "cement", "certifi", "charset-normalizer", "colorlog", "google-auth", "hmd-cli-app", "hmd-cli-tools", "idna", "inquirerpy", "jinja2", "jmespath", "kubernetes", "markupsafe", "oauthlib", "pfzy", "prompt-toolkit", "pyasn1", "pyasn1-modules", "python-dateutil", "python-dotenv", "pyyaml", "requests", "requests-oauthlib", "rsa", "s3transfer", "six", "urllib3", "wcwidth", "websocket-client"], "summary": "CLI tools for configuring other HMD tools", "upload_time": 1704922751}, "documentation": ["# HMD CLI Configure\n\nThis package is a command line utility for configuring your local environment to use other HMD CLI tools.\nAll configuration for HMD CLI tools is done via a dotenv file located at `$HMD_HOME/.config/hmd.env`.\nThe path `$HMD_HOME` must be set by you to a directory that will be used with HMD tools only, and be present in your session.\nIt is a good idea to set this in a `.bash_profile` or similar file.\n\n## Usage\n\nIn order to set an environment variable in the `hmd.env` file, you would use the `set-env` command and provide `key` and `value` arguments.\n\n```\nhmd configure set-env <key> <value>\n```\n\nThis will update or append the following line in `hmd.env`: `key='value'`.\n\n## Common Variables\n\nThere are some common variables that you might what to set upon first installation.\n\n- `HMD_GH_USERNAME`: the GitHub username to use when connecting; primarily used by `hmd-cli-mickey` to fetch remote templates\n- `HMD_GH_PASSWORD`: either a GitHub PAT or absolute path to file containing only the PAT. The entire file contents will be read and used.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.hmd_cli_configure", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.VERSION_BANNER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.hostname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.hmd_home_vars", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.default_env_vars", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController", "bases": ["Controller"], "methods": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController._default", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.set_env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.get_env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.list_env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.Meta", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.Meta.label", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.Meta.alias", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hmd_cli_configure.controller.LocalController.Meta.stacked_type", "type": null, "documen